.TH "phylink_mii_ioctl" 9 "phylink_mii_ioctl" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
phylink_mii_ioctl \- generic mii ioctl interface
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" phylink_mii_ioctl
.BI "(struct phylink *pl "  ","
.BI "struct ifreq *ifr "  ","
.BI "int cmd "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pl" 12
a pointer to a \fIstruct phylink\fP returned from \fBphylink_create\fP
.IP "ifr" 12
a pointer to a \fIstruct ifreq\fP for socket ioctls
.IP "cmd" 12
ioctl cmd to execute
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Perform the specified MII ioctl on the PHY attached to the phylink instance
specified by \fIpl\fP. If no PHY is attached, emulate the presence of the PHY.

SIOCGMIIPHY:
read register from the current PHY.
SIOCGMIIREG:
read register from the specified PHY.
SIOCSMIIREG:
set a register on the specified PHY.
.SH "RETURN"
zero on success or negative error code.
